<br>
Group consists of a necro, cleric and wizard.  Necro and cleric are on the isle with main party.   Wizard is group leader and ports new raid members up to 1st isle.  New raid member aggroes a mob on 1st isle and dies.  Wizard ports back down, picks new raid member and ports back.  Necro summons new raid members corpse up to main party.  Cleric rezzes.  <br>
<br>
Basically its an exploit to bypass content but you won't get into any trouble for using it.<br>
<br>
Kebkin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oligith>Oligith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf of Many Faces</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/03 2:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/10869.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mage 7th Island PoA raid</span><hr size=1> I am too young to attend, but I know someone who if you ask really nicely, might be able to give you some advice on PoA raids by the name of Valquiss in Saga.  He'll probably mind wipe me for saying this, but he has led numerous raids there for the Fellowship and has made it to at least isle 6 in those raids.  Further than that I can't be certain, but I will post a few raid links of how he prepared this for you so you can have some of your questions answered.<br>
